data.name: TextBox1.Text
data.value:
Welcome to the Chatterbox Help Topics.
These topics will help you get started with the program.
Click on the labels to the right to access a help topic.
Notice: These help topics may be outdated. For the most updated topics, please visit:
http://hotlandsoftware.x10hosting.com
Help topics updated on 3/19/2016

data.name: TextBox2.Text
data.value:
Chatterbox is a LAN instant messaging tool designed for small-to- medium sized businesses, home servers, and home users. It is designed to be extremely lightweight and easy to use.
It was developed by Hotland Software (formerly ServoSoft Inc.)
Chatterbox was first released on 11/18/2014 as Chatterbox 0.01, and gradually became what it is today.
For more information on this build in particular, go to the main program, click on "Help", then click on "About".

data.name: TextBox3.Text
data.value:
To connect with another user, type in their computer's unique IP address. Please note that this is not the same as your network's IP address, although it is also an IPv4 number.
To find this number, open the Command Prompt by either hitting the Windows key + R, or clicking the link below.
You will see a black terminal line with text. Click this window, and type in the words "ipconfig" (no quotes). Then, find your current adapter that is in use (it may have a name such as Ethernet adapter Local Area Connection, or something similar). When you do, you will find this:
IPv4 Address. . . . . . . . . . . : (IP)
Write down this IP on a paper, or type this IP into a Notepad. Then give it to your partner(s).
If you are connecting to another user, have them repeat the instructions above. Then, connect to their IP, and have them connect to yours as well.
Afterwards, you will have an established connection! Happy chatting!

data.name: TextBox5.Text
data.value:
To change the language of the program follow these steps: Open the main program. Click on "Settings". Click the Language dropdown box. Select the language you want. Click Save Settings. Click Close.
(Note, the Help Topics are currently only available in English.)

data.name: TextBox6.Text
data.value:
Chatterbox v2.02 will be the final edition to use .NET Framework 2.0.
From v2.03 and onwards, we will be moving to .NET Framework 3.0 and eventually to .NET Framework 4.0.
There are however no plans to move Chatterbox EME to .NET Framework 3.0 as of right now.
It is highly recommended to get the latest operating system. We recommend using Windows Vista at minimum for Chatterbox in the future.
